  "description": "The adhesive rolling resistance linear model is based on the rolling resistance linear model, to which an adhesive component is added. It is a linear-based model that can be installed at both ball-ball and ball-facet contacts, and is referred to in commands and FISH by the name arrlinear .",
  "typical_applications": [
    "Cohesive granular materials with rolling resistance",
    "Wet / sticky soils and powders",
    "Repose-angle studies with adhesion",
    "Fine-particle agglomeration"
  ],
